description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Corporate Quality Manager Band 7 – Corporate Quality &amp; Regulation Team  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashford and St Peters Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is looking for an experienced governance and risk professional work in our challenging but rewarding Corporate Quality and Regulation Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our aim is to provide a caring and professional service to ensure that all colleagues, stakeholders, and members of the public receive the best service when they liaise with our team.  We seek to deliver the Trust’s Strategy in all that we do in a proactive and sensitive manner, giving service users the best possible service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who has significant experience in driving forward corporate quality and regulation in a proactive and strategic way who can demonstrate service improvement through robust governance and risk management.  You must have experience working in this kind of role the NHS, ideally in an acute Trust. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have experience in the functions of corporate governance, clinical governance, risk, assurance, audit, safety, clinical effectiveness.  You must be experienced generating and handling papers for high level Corporate Committees and be able to produce reports using excellent written style, grammar and with high quality technical content which is ‘right first time’.  You must have robust data and information analytic skills and be highly numerate and excellent at using IT systems effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be excellent dealing with NHS service users, colleagues, and external organisations such as regulatory bodies or NHS partners.  Having the right attitude to keep calm in this fast pace service is vital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we offer opportunities for learning and development, access to the NHS Pension Scheme, work perks, NHS Discounts, opportunities for flexible working and on-site childcare provision (nursery).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is advertised Monday to Friday 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please email jo.finch1@nhs.net or phone 01932 72 2125.&lt;/p&gt;
